[[File:Saura Script invented by Mangei Gomango.jpg|thumb|300px|Saura Script invented by Mangei Gomango]] '''Mangei Gomango''' popularly known as '''Pandita Sabara Mangei Gamango''' is said to have devised<ref>{{cite web|url=http://as1.ori.nic.in/atlcdemo/?refid=Activities&pgid=publication |title=Academy Of Tribal Languages And Culture: Publication |publisher=As1.ori.nic.in |date= |accessdate=2015-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sealang.net/sala/archives/pdf4/zide1999three.pdf |format=PDF |title=Three Munda Scripts |author=Norman Zide |publisher=Sealang.net |accessdate=2015-04-16}}</ref> the tribal language of [[Rayagada district]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=ospMAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA901&lpg=PA901&dq=Mangei+Gomango&source=bl&ots=9cItlhdV7u&sig=p5i5p2agrJSHn3_LhteOZOWyHsg&hl=en&sa=X&ei=02b0VNfnDM6VuQTrm4KgAg&ved=0CDUQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=Mangei%20Gomango&f=false |title=The World's Writing Systems - Peter T. Daniels, William Bright - Google Books |publisher=Books.google.co.in |date= |accessdate=2015-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ko.cyclopaedia.asia/wiki/Sorang_Sompeng_alphabet |title=Sorang Sompeng alphabet &#124; 인터넷 사이트 &#124; cyclopaedia.net |publisher=Ko.cyclopaedia.asia |date=2008-01-02 |accessdate=2015-04-16}}</ref> He has been awarded by Odisha Sahitya Academy.<ref name=Sambadepaper>{{cite news|last1=Mishra|first1=Nilanchala|title=Saura Script & Saura Cult|url=http://sambadepaper.com/Details.aspx?id=174748&boxid=5617284|accessdate=30 June 2015|publisher=Sambadepaper|date=30 June 2015}}</ref>
==Early life== Gomango was born on 16 June 1916 in Marichaguda, [[Rayagada district|Rayagada]], [[Odisha]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://inpr.odisha.gov.in/Download/index-or.pdf |format=PDF |title=Orissa Review : Index 1948-2005 |publisher=Inpr.odisha.gov.in |accessdate=2015-04-16}}</ref> He is regarded as the inventor of Soura Lilp(dialect). The Saura script [[Sorang Sompeng alphabet|Sorang Sompeng]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=ospMAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA612&dq=Sorang+Sompeng&hl=en&sa=X&ei=wsLyVLuFCpWHuATqtoD4Cg&ved=0CBwQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Sorang%20Sompeng&f=false |title=The World's Writing Systems - Peter T. Daniels, William Bright - Google Books |publisher=Books.google.co.in |date= |accessdate=2015-04-16}}</ref> was developed by Mangei Gamang in 1966 for spreading the language.<ref name="New Indian Express">{{cite news|title=Government agrees to conduct survey on Saura script|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/article1516329.ece|accessdate=25 June 2015|agency=Express News Service|publisher=New Indian Express|date=25 March 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Alan Wood |url=http://www.alanwood.net/unicode/sora-sompeng.html |title=Sora Sompeng – Test for Unicode support in Web browsers |publisher=Alanwood.net |date= |accessdate=2015-04-16}}</ref> As a mark of respect, people called him "Pandita Sabara" (scholar).<ref name=Samayaraprtiphalana>{{cite journal|last1=Dash|first1=Bimalashankar|title=Akhara bramha in Metra Hill|issue=June 16-30 2015|pages=04|url=https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=983599125005390&set=a.192735864091724.45220.100000659360641&type=1&theater|accessdate=29 June 2015}}</ref>
==Works== The temple of Matarabnam in Marichaguda played a great role in the invention of the script. It is believed that there the Sorang Sompeng alphabet came to him in a vision on 18 June 1936.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.omniglot.com/writing/sorangsompeng.htm |title=Sorang Sompeng script |publisher=Omniglot.com |date=1936-06-18 |accessdate=2015-04-16}}</ref> He was a poet, Arurvedic scholar and a reformer too. In 1936, he established a press in Puthasahi of Gunupur Sub division for spreading the script he invented.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-otherstates/in-danger-of-extinction/article1818261.ece |title=In danger of extinction |publisher=Thehindu.com |date=2007-03-31 |accessdate=2015-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/blogs/anukumar/3645/64936/my-fathers-circles-of-life.html |title=Anu Kumar's Blog : My father's Circles of Life |publisher=Ibnlive.in.com |date=2013-11-11 |accessdate=2015-04-16}}</ref>
