== Third Crusade ==
'''1187'''
* ''October.'' Conrad sends [[Joscius, Archbishop of Tyre]] to Europe to ask for a new crusade.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=72}}
* ''October 29.'' [[Pope Gregory VIII]] declares the [[Third Crusade]] in his bull ''[[Audita tremendi]]''.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=72}}
* ''November 25.'' Saladin lays [[Siege of Tyre (1187)|siege to Tyre]].{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=314}}
'''1188'''
* ''January 1.'' Saladin abandons the siege of Tyre.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=315}}
* ''May.'' Saladin releases Guy.{{sfn|Philips|2010|p=141}}
* ''October.'' A Sicilian fleet arrives at the Holy Land.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=73}}
* ''November'' Saladin's troops capture Kerak.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=73}}{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=322}}
* ''December 6.'' Safad is captured by Saladin's troops.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=73}}{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=322}}
'''1189'''
* ''January 5.'' Belvoir surrenders to Saladin's troops.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=73}}{{sfn|Barber|2012|pp=315-316}}
* ''May.'' Saladin's troops capture Montreal. Only Tyre and [[Beaufort Castle, Lebanon|Belfort]] remain under Frank rule in the Kingdom of Jerusalem.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=74}}
* ''August.'' Guy's brother, [[Geoffrey I of Lusignan]], informs him about the preparations for a new crusade in Europe. They gather 9000 troops and march to Tyre, but Conrad does not allow Guy to enter the town.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=74}}{{sfn|Barber|2012|pp=330-331}}
* ''August 26.'' Guy lays siege to Acre with the support of a Pisan fleet.{{sfn|Philips|2010|p=141}}{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=74}}
* ''September.'' Flemish, Danish, Frisian and French crusaders arrive at Acre.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=333}}
* ''October 4.'' Saladin defeats the crusaders at Acre. Fearing of an epidemic, he leaves Acre, but he appoints his brother, [[Al-Adil I|Al-Adil]], to command his troops.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=332}}
'''1190'''
* ''Easter.'' Conrad acknowledges Guy as the lawful king in return for the confirmation of his rule of Tyre.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=337}}
* ''June 10.'' [[Frederick I, Holy Roman Emperor]] drowns in the [[Saleph River]] in Asia Minor during [[Third Crusade#Barbarossa's crusade|his crusade]].{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=75}}{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=328}}
* ''Summer.'' Patriarch Heraclius dies at Acre.{{sfn|Hamilton|2016|p=84}}
* ''July 27.'' Henry II, Count of Champagne arrives at Acre, taking new troops and funds with him.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=334}}
* ''July 29.'' Sybilla and her two daughters by Guy die at Acre.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=75}}{{sfn|Philips|2010|p=144}}
* ''Early October.'' [[Frederick VI, Duke of Swabia]] and the remnants of Frederick I's crusade arrive at Acre. A hospital is established for them at the crusaders' camp.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=335}}{{sfn|Tyerman|2006|p=257}}{{sfn|Jotischky|2017|p=89}}
* ''{{circa}} November 20.'' Guy's opponents persuade the papal legate, [[Ubaldo Lanfranchi|Ubaldo of Pisa]], to annul the marriage of Humphrey IV and Isabella.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=335}}
* ''November 24.'' Conrad marries Isabella in Tyre to strengthen his position against Guy.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=335}}
'''1191'''
* ''April 20.'' [[Philip II of France|Philip II, King of France]], and the French crusaders land at Acre. He acknowledges Conrad's claim to the throne against Guy.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=76}}{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=344}}
* ''May 6–June 1.'' Richard I, King of England conquers Cyprus.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=343}}
* ''May 11.'' Guy meets with Richard I in Cyprus.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=76}}{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=343}}
* ''June 8.'' Richard I disembarks at Acre.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=343}}
* ''July 12.'' The garrisons of Acre surrender to the crusaders in return for a safe passage.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=346}}{{sfn|Philips|2010|p=151}}
* ''July 24 or 26.'' Richard I and Philip II confirm Guy's right to rule the kingdom until his death, but they also stipulate that Conrad is to succeed Guy on the throne.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=77}}{{sfn|Philips|2010|p=152}}
* ''July 31.'' Philip II departs for France.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=346}}
* ''August 20.'' Richard I decides to continue the military campaign and orders the massacre of 2,700 Muslim prisoners.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=347}}
* ''September 7.'' [[Battle of Arsuf]]: Richard I overcomes Saladin.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=348}}{{sfn|Philips|2010|pp=155-156}}
* ''September 10.'' Richard I seizes Jaffa without resistance.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=349}}
* ''October.'' Richard I offers the hands of his sister, [[Joan of England, Queen of Sicily|Joan]], to Al-Adil, proposing that they could jointly rule the restored kingdom, but she refuses to marry a Muslim.{{sfn|Barber|2012|pp=350-351}}{{sfn|Maalouf|1984|pp=212-213}}
* ''{{circa}} November 15.'' Conrad proposes a separate peace to Saladin who informs the crusaders about Conrad's offer.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=351}}
'''1192'''
* ''Januar 20.'' The crusaders seize the abandoned Ascalon.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=77}}
* ''April 16.'' After Richard decides to return to England, the Frank barons persuade him to acknowledge Conrad as the lawful king.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=77}}
* ''April 28.'' Assassins murder Conrad in Tyre.{{sfn|Lock|2006|p=77}}{{sfn|Philips|2010|p=158}}
* ''May.'' Richard I authorizes Guy to purchase Cyprus from the Templars.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=352}}
* ''May 5.'' Henry II of Champagne marries Conrad's pregnant widow, Isabella in Acre.{{sfn|Barber|2012|p=352}}{{sfn|Philips|2010|p=159}}
* ''June 11.'' The crusaders march as far as [[Bayt Nuba]] near Jerusalem, but Richard I decides not to attack the Holy City in fear of being deprived of water.{{sfn|Philips|2010|pp=160-161}}{{sfn|Tyerman|2006|p=467}}
